content.detailedDescription: My daughters and i were driving east on i-24 in tennessee. the lights seemed to be hovering over the trees to the southeast of my location. we were driving, so it was hard to tell. i thought they were possibly helicopters from a nearby air national guard base. they seemed to remain stationary as we drove right under them. there were four bright points of white lights shaped in a crescent with a twinkling reddish/white in the center of the four brighter points of light. i have lived in this area most of my life and have never witnessed anything like this before. we continued on to our destination writing it off as what we thought it had to be, helicopters. but, curiosity got the best of me....
content.summary: My daughters and i witnessed lights in the sky while driving eastbound on i-24 in tn.

content.detailedDescription: I was taking an evening walk in rothamsted park, harpenden, hertforshire, england as i often did then. at that time i lived nearby at 8 longcroft avenue, harpenden, hertfordshire, england. shortly after entering the park i looked up at the clear night sky and noticed an unusual ball of orange/red light traversing the sky slowly at a fixed altitude and direction coming from approx. nw. it was larger than any star and initially i thought it might be a aircraft, however it was noiseless and exhibited no flashing white navigation light, nor a red or green wing light. at this point i felt transfixed by the object and became fearful as it was travelling in my direction and something felt 'odd' about it. i would estimate that when it was about a mile away it made a 90 degree turn to the se, maintaining height and the same speed (comparable, say, to a piston engined aircraft at cruise speed). as it turned, the shape mutated into an oval and again i saw no navigation lights that one might expect as it did so. the object then continued on this new track for a minute or two and then rapidly accelerated at an amazing rate, continuing on the same course, again with no sound and disappeared from view as it shrank due to distance. i was riveted to the spot for a while and felt deeply disturbed with my arm hair 'on end'. i returned home quickly. the following day, i reported my observation to the local newspaper, the herts advertiser, who expressed no interest but curiously, about a week later, while in the garden of my home at about the same time i saw another light in the sky approaching me. this was identifiably a large plane which flew over my home at a very low height of only a few hundred feet which aircraft are not supposed to do. i imagined that this was some kind of deliberate act to discourage my 'ufo sighting'. in that era there was no internet or anyone else i could think of to report this. i only today happened to visit your site and found the 'report a sighting' link, so i did so. out of curiosity i searched online for 'ufo sighting harpenden' and found 2 links to articles in the same newspaper i originally contacted decades ago, both in this area, one very nearby, dated july 2009 and sep 2010. i can provide links to my observation point on google maps and those 2 newspaper articles. apologies for this late submission but i'm glad that it is now reported. it still makes my hair stand on end when i think about it.
content.summary: Noiseless light that changed direction then accelerated away very fast

content.detailedDescription:
I was walking back from work, which is about 5 kilometres or so from where the sighting happened. keep in mind i work until 1:00 a.M, so my sighting took place in the middle of the night. i always like to watch the clouds when i walk. i was following my usual routine of watching the clouds move, when i caught something out of the corner of my eye. it was a large semi-triangular object, and it seemed that it came out from behind the clouds. i thought it was a plane until i saw the flashing lights on the side of it were not the typical lights that you would see on an airplane. they were yellow, green and white and the flashed in a pattern of green, then white, then yellow, repeatedly. i would say the craft was approximately 30-40 feet long and 15 feet tall. it was moving in a fairly straight line. it started out going northeast, then made a sharp turn and headed true north until i could not see it anymore. it also made a unexplainable sound, similar to the sound of high frequency. obviously at this point i  realized i was not looking at an ordinary aircraft. i watched it until it disappeared. then i ran home and now i am writing this report. 

p.S. i forgot to mention that i'm pretty sure it had 1 central rectangular window on each side of the triangle, although this may have been metal, or some type of pattern.
content.summary: Saw what i believe to be a ufo.

content.detailedDescription:
This involves a train trip my brother took in april 1981 from tucson, az to el paso, tx. 

i am submitting this event in case it correlates with some other report you may have received from the same time and place. 

west of a small city in new mexico which my brother believes is deming, the train conductor came through the car and instructed everyone on the south side (right side) of the train to pull down the window shades and not to look out the window. my brother pulled down the shade, but peeked behind it. he saw a freeway beside the track (i-10) filled with stopped emergency vehicles - police cars, ambulances, fire trucks.  this continued for miles.  it was just before noon. the weather was good. the track and freeway are about 35 miles from the mexican border. the area is quite arid and sparsely populated.  my brother stopped in el paso, tx for 2 days and examined the tv news and newspapers for reports on the incident. there was no information at all - nothing about a freeway closure or the hundreds of emergency vehicles stretched along i-10. 

 it is unlikely to have involved a nuclear test due to the close proximity to the international border and to deming.
content.summary: Not a ufo sighting. it is an odd event which could relate.

content.detailedDescription: We were walking down the gillespie st when i spotted it stationary over the field in the east past snowhill. it looked like a cloud but you could tell it wasn't because it wasn't moving with the wind. sort of liked it was cloaked??? i asked my friends (there was 5 of us) if they saw it and they agreed it wasn't a cloud. nothing happened when it was just me who noticed it. as soon as i mentioned it to everyone else, any of us looking in its area kept seeing stars (like if you'd just been hit in the head) and looked away. when we looked back we almost didn't find it again. we had continued walking when a black heli looked like it was going to fly past it then it flew straight through it and it dissipated ?? sort of.... the heli flew away, an after image of the object was still there, and the star effect was still active. the two freakiest things about the whole encounter is there was no sound until i mentioned it to someone else and when i tried to record it my phone battery *died* at 95%. this is not the first time in the last 3 months i've seen something extraterrestrial in the sky and it probably wont be the last.
content.summary: Cloaked object in the sky, messed with my vision when i mentioned it out loud to others,

content.detailedDescription: I was walking sweeney ridge trail today, sunny blue skies with huge cumulus clouds after morning rain. while admiring the clouds i noticed what appeared to be a stationary, thin, short, dark line at an angle leaning to the right, not unlike the backslash on a typewriter/computer keyboard. it seemed quite far above, higher than the air traffic/planes commonly seen flying along the pacific coast. while watching the object and trying to figure out what it was, 2 more appeared close by and sidled up alongside the first, all at the same angle. after some minutes, they suddenly were no longer to be seen. the incident lasted about 15 minutes. i continued my hike, frequently scanning the shy, but saw no other air born irregularities :)
content.summary: Walking sweeney ridge saw what looked like keyboard backslash high above. while watching 2 more appeared along side then vanished.

content.detailedDescription:
While at a sales conference at the red rocks resort i had just gotten ready for my walk to the conference center somewhere between 7:15-7:40am. remembering i told my family i would take a photo from my hotel of the beautiful landscape and the vegas city skyline. i opened my curtain on this sunny morning. i got my phone ready and began to scan the view for the best picture. after a quick glance i noticed a hot air balloon to the right it was a typical looking hot air balloon. i looked to the left side of my window and noticed a dark shape that seemed contrast in color and shape against the mountain chain. i looked a few moments longer and thought wow that large shape is actually moving. i starred for a few moments and came to the firm conclusion that the object was indeed moving slowly left to right from my viewpoint. after a few minutes of personal viewing i thought i might take a video cause no one will believe me. so i began to take video and a short time into it the video stopped and a message of lack of storage came up. i thought to myself- i should have bought the 32gb phone. any way, i took a few moments to clear up some storage glancing up to make sure the craft was still there, and it was still moving almost hovering as it had been doing. i cleared the necessary memory and began to take a picture and video again. i wondered what it could be moving so slow it didn't look like any blimps i have seen at sporting events. it was moving too slow for conventional aircraft, it seemed large for a drone. at one point i quickly pan to the right to see the hot air balloon i had seen earlier to give some perspective. in addition, you can see cars driving underneath. while the first video is a bit shaky i made sure to lean on the window support to try to steady the video. after about four minutes i stopped recording because i had get my rear downstairs to work my booth at our convention. honestly i do not know what it is which is why i have submitted it to you. i would be interested to hear what the locals or experts have to say about its identity. 

summary, seemingly large craft dark in color, moving left to right somewhat steady buy very slow almost hovering. traveling toward las vegas.
content.summary: Slow moving craft moving toward las vegas

content.detailedDescription: I had been thinking about a previous encounter that had happened 10 years ago an hour or so earlier and had been watching a comic book series on my laptop. i opened the window to have a cigarette and saw three flashing lights in the shape of a triangle moving slowly north easterly. i recognized it immediately as a ufo. the blinking was slow and the craft was barely visible when not blinking yet it reappeared in irregular places as if it was projecting itself slightly each time. it had no constant light as you'd find on a plane nor did it make a sound (it was close enough to hear had it been "current" technology) and had a fuzzy aura around it when visible. i continued to watch it calmly and tried to communicate telepathically asking it to come closer as i had done once before. this time it didn't. i watched it disappear behind the houses to the north east of me. i wanted to run outside to continue watching it but wasn't suitably clothed. i felt as if the air was charged with static electricity. i live around 15 miles from an airport and there are planes passing in the night sky regularly on the same trajectory, this craft followed a different one, was much closer and again, made no sound. i wasn't surprised to see this as i've seen objects of varying description a number of times yet i was intrigued given the fact that i had been thinking about the same type of ufo earlier on.
content.summary: Slow triangle shaped, 3 blinking lights, seemed to disappear/reappear

content.detailedDescription:
Spending much of my childhood years on the u.S. naval base in guantanamo bay, cuba had its share of adventure and intrigue. sometime between 1999 and 2001 (before the base was built up to the max security detention center it is, today), some friends and i were en route to another friend's house in the 'nob hill' neighborhood right at the base of skyline drive (skyline drive x 1st street) and were dropped off by our one friend's mom. it was a clear, pitch black night with no street lights around the immediate vicinity of us. after being dropped off, we proceeded to walk to our friend's house when one of us noticed a very bright white star that seemed out of place. after we got everyone's attention and pointed up to it, it seemed to realize we were observing it. at this time, the bright white orb/star began to perform some amazing maneuvers that included rapid acceleration, deceleration, zig-zag patterns, and circles in the sky. we were stunned and i couldn't move an inch. we were teenagers and scared out of our minds! i don't want to attribute my inability to run away from this event to this being/craft/entity, but anything is possible, i suppose. when we watched it for a few more seconds, another identical bright white orb joined the first orb and they began to circle/dance around each other in a circle pattern. we could not believe our eyes and didn't know what to do. it wasn't long after the second orb appeared and they circled each other that one orb shot straight off into space in an instance while the other, remaining orb appeared to grow in size as if it were getting closer to us. at this point, we could not contain ourselves any longer and ran as fast as we could to our friends house. our parents picked us up shortly after and i will never forget this event. it still makes the hair raise up on my entire body every time i tell the story. there was no sound and the maneuvers were amazing to watch. 

since the event, i have given my testimony (along with 2 other witnesses who were with me that night) on the history channel's ufo hunters tv series with bill birnes. i felt compelled to contact the ufo hunters about this event while in college watching ufo hunters on tv when a navy petty officer gave his testimony of two bright white orbs in guantanamo bay, cuba on the navy base (same location) a few years prior to our sighting. he claimed that he was out on a pier one night and noticed two bright white orbs circling each other underwater and then shot away without ever coming up into the air. since he saw the exact same entities performing the exact same maneuvers in the exact same location within a few years of our sighting, i had to share! maybe the waters around cuba hold more secrets than we currently know of? 

there is also a facebook group for past 'gtmo' (guantanamo bay nas abbreviation) residents that i am a part of where other people have come forward about sightings similar to mine over the years in different locations on the base, including mccalla airfield. 

once you see/experience an extraordinary and utterly unbelievable event like this in your lifetime, you become very open-minded and accepting of any possibilities. the exact coordinates of our sighting via google maps was 19.933280, -75.109474 and we were facing west northwest while observing the event. from this location, the active airfield is approx. 5.9 miles southwest (mugm).
content.flightPath: Stationary,Hovering then path,Straight-line path,Path with directional change,Path then hovering
content.summary: Two bright orbs over nas gtmo observed by five witnesses performing unreal maneuvers

content.detailedDescription: I work on main st. in west orange, nj. just one hour ago i exited one of the buildings at my workplace and saw what i thought was a white plastic supermarket bag drifting along high up in the sky. i looked up at it because i knew it was not an aircraft, as it initially seemed to drift along. it looked like the wind was slowly taking it. i waited to see if it would drop because there is no wind today and thought it was riding on a high wind current, like hawks do. it then continued to steadily move and remained high in the sky. it was a white light that continuously turned on and off the entire time. i managed to round up 3 fellow employees and we all continued to watch it. i was thrilled and excited that i was able to get 3 witnesses to watch it with me in the courtyard at my workplace. we walked further backwards because it was being blocked by the building rooftop, so it apparently was moving further southeast. once we did this, it either drifted further away or disappeared as we could not see it anymore.

content.detailedDescription: This is the second time i've seen this ball of light. the first time was several months back. i've worked on flight lines and lived near air bases and i'm familiar with many (most perhaps) of flying vehicles. i've also spent a considerable amount of time watching satellites traverse the night sky. the first time i saw it (this ball of light), it was a really clear night and the object was very bright, it moved steady across the sky in a straight line sw to ne... i highly doubt it was a satellite due to the size. i'd say it was big as a bayer aspirin on the tip of my thumb with my hand extended straight out in front of me. however, i didn't report it because "it could have been". i am reporting this second event because there were clouds in the sky, and this object was traveling below them. exact same description - solid ball of white light, no faa lights, no head lights, no sign of exhaust, and no (additional) sound. there were several other aircraft about the sky before, during, and after this incident. there was at least one fixed wing, propeller craft that was present in the w/nw sky - it was traveling in circles - i assume a pilot practicing or just logging hours. several higher flying aircraft were seen and heard as well. i could hear the propeller driven craft and two or three jet craft that passed over before and after we (me and my nine year old daughter) lost sight of the ball of light. i have to kick myself for not having my camera more readily available. i am going to assume that i will see this again and i plan to have my camera closer by.
content.summary: White ball of light - no faa lights, lamps, or exhaust lights.

thank you for all y'all do!

content.detailedDescription: At approximately 7:30pm in early october 2013 i let my dogs out in my west facing front yard and i saw a white orb eject itself out of the ocean from a distance of between 9-10 miles to me. object came to an immediate low altitude hover over the ocean. i immediately knew what i was looking at so i ran inside and told my girlfriend to get out of the house. she ran out and i pointed to the object. she then ran in the house to find a camera. then i yelled at it (with only my mind as it was still 9-10 miles from me). the orb then came head on at me, in a laser straight line, and coasted to a stop directly over my head. it covered the 9-10 miles, and literally  coasted half of those miles, in under 4 seconds. orb was approximately 500 feet sitting directly over my head for about 20 seconds. i made no further attempt to communicate with it an received no communication back from the object. i was jumping up and down like i just won the lottery with my head back as far as it could go watching the object sitting motionless directly over my head. it was easily the happiest moment of my life. my dogs did not detect object at all. 3 people across the street saw me jumping up and down and waving my hands over my head and walked over to me and asked me if i was ok. before one of the people from across the street reached me, the orb immediately went in reverse back to its original location over marina del rey. i told him i was fine and he went back across the street. my girlfriend then ran outside with the camera. orb was too far away at that point and wandered north west, up the coast, out of site. orb was covered in a thick white plasma. it looked like a perfect tesla coil covered in plasma. no structure was seen through the plasma.
content.flightPath: Stationary,Hovering then path,Straight-line path,Path then hovering
content.summary: Orb ejected itself out of the ocean (marina del rey), hovered (low altitude), i yelled at it with only my mind. orb then flew directly at me covering a distance of 9-10 miles in under 4 seconds and came to a dead hover directly over my head.

content.detailedDescription: It was 8:24pm and i went outside to grab something from my car when i noticed something in the sky that looked like a really bright star.  as i stared at it for a moment another one appeared next to it, and at that time my 8 year old son came outside and i told him to look, and right as i said that, another one appeared next to the other two in a straight line.  i then told him to go inside and get his grandma, and when she came outside another one aligned with the previous 3. the objects hovered in the same spot for a few minutes and then began to gradually move away from each other.  two of them faded away while the other two stayed blinking in the same spot.  we could see more, but my camera couldn't get them to show up on it. we were watching these objects fly around for about 10 minutes before we saw about 3 airplanes start flying through the area.  in one of the videos you can hear something that sounds like gun shots, but i'm not sure if that came from them.  the objects would still stay in place for the most part when the airplanes would fly by them.  the objects seemed to be about 3-4 times the size of the airplanes. we spotted at least 6 different objects all in different areas.  some of the objects were moving and getting brighter, while others just appeared bright in the sky and faded away.  we watched for about 30 minutes and we filmed a lot of it.  we went inside because it was a little chilly out, but we kept going back outside to see if they were still there.  we would see one or two, but not as many as we had at first.  one of the times i went outside, i saw one that was red, but it only appeared for a minuted or so.  the skies were clear and the stars looks a bluish white while these objects looked like a bright yellow light.  this was the most surreal thing i have ever seen.  at first i thought it was maybe something the military was doing, but it didn't make any sense because the military base is the complete opposite direction and none of it looked like any of our aircraft.  the more we watched, the more scared i became.  i wasn't sure if it was something from outer space or aircraft from another country.  i called my brother to go outside of his house after watching them for about 25 minutes.  he went outside and he saw two of them.  at first he didn't see them but i told him to keep watching and he would see one light up.  after about a minute, he saw one.  i left my mothers house around 9:15 and drove about 2 miles to my house.  on my way to my house i could see one clear in the sky.  i went to my neighbors house and had them come take a look, but only one could really see.  from my house they were kind of hidden behind a tree, so it was hard to see.  he saw two of them appear and then i had to go inside to put my son to sleep.  when i went back outside around 10:30pm they were completely gone.  i couldn't stop thinking about them all day today, and i was sure that something would be on social media or the news, but i saw nothing.  i sent 3 different news stations my footage, but two of the 3 didn't respond, and one sent me a message stating i could email the
